net.smartcosmos.objects.model.context

Interface IFile

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAccountContext, IAccountDomainResource<IFile>, IDomainResource<IFile>, IMoniker, IReferentialObject, IUrnNamespace
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    File

    public interface IFile
extends IAccountDomainResource<IFile>, IReferentialObject
    Represents any type of multimedia file that is explicitly associated with a single IReferentialObject. If a file needs to be shared with multiple objects, developers should design and implement a novel scheme using IRelationship definitions (recommended) or IMetadata (alternative).

      • isPending

        boolean isPending()
        Indicates if the file is defined in the data store but not yet physically uploaded to the file store. Extensions can easily determine if the file's actual content is available by watching for EventType.FileUploaded
        Returns:
        true, if only the data store record exists and the file contents are not yet available
        See Also:
        EventType.FileDefined, EventType.FileUploaded

        String getUrl()
        Private, internal, secured URL that callers generally do not have permissions to directly access. The URL stored here is served up indirectly through the appropriate SnapBundle file endpoint.

        Internal, private, secure, and typically inaccessible internally managed URL depicting where the file is stored

      • getDigitalSignature

        String getDigitalSignature()
        JSON structure that represents two distinct digital signatures, a signature of the actual file contents upon submission to the platform and a second signature of the metadata used to describe the file definition (including the digital signature of the file itself).

        The JSON digital signature block also includes narrative on how the digital signatures were generated, including algorithm, iterations, and the actual library used. A prototypical example of a digital signature JSON block is below for reference:

        {
        "algorithm": "SHA-256",
        "description": "The contentsSignature is of the file contents exclusively. The root signature is of the signedBody exclusively",
        "iterations": 1,
        "library": "Apache Shiro (Java)",
        "signature": "8ae65ce110ab15fbea8df6e61adedaf9ca36dc02ebcd5d451da0f7d18a790abe",
        "signedBody":
          {
            "accountUrn": "urn:uuid:9728d95e-9ae5-482f-84a7-b8f1fce80389",
            "contentsSignature": "8F866F53645218F77957675EC197678F2F9D3155455A01FF6F4E6FF68C5696C7",
            "entityReferenceType": "ObjectInteraction",
            "fileUrn": "urn:uuid:5655cf2d-a843-4d7b-941d-c3abe70a007b",
            "referenceUrn": "urn:uuid:6889da4e-7fed-49b5-821b-b5a9f06740d4",
            "url": "https://net.tagdynamics.snapbundle.stage.s3.amazonaws.blahblahblahblah/file.mp4"
          }
        }

        Returns:
        JSON structure describing the digital signature
